parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended engagement of the AEB system can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop, increasing the risk of rear-end collisions, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops or brakes hard without warning
often with no obstacles or vehicles in front of it. The "BRAKE" warning light may flash on the dashboard
and the brakes may engage even when the driver's foot is not on the pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Faulty Front Camera or Sensor Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty front camera or sensor can cause the AEB system to malfunction, leading to unintended braking or false warnings.
symptoms: The "BRAKE" warning light may flash on the dashboard
and the brakes may engage even when there are no obstacles or vehicles in front of the vehicle. The system may also incorrectly detect objects or vehicles
leading to false warnings or unintended braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EPS system can cause the steering wheel to stick or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels sticky or difficult to turn
the steering wheel sticks to the left or right
audible clicking or grinding sounds when turning
and loss of power steering assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause multiple system failures, including the power steering system, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights on the dashboard
loss of power steering assist
and failure of other systems such as brakes and transmission.
